quizzes.textContent:
[h1]The if Statement[/h1]

The [b]if [/b]statement is a conditional statement that executes a block of code when a condition is true.
The general form of the [b]if [/b]statement is: [code format="cs" ][b]if[/b] (condition)
{
    // Execute this code when condition is [b]true[/b]
}[/code]
The condition can be any expression that returns true or false. 
For example: [code format="cs" codeId="827"]static void Main(string[] args)
{
   int x = 8;
   int y = 3;
 
   [b]if[/b] (x > y)
   { 
      Console.WriteLine("x is greater than y");
   }
}[/code]
The code above will evaluate the condition [b]x > y[/b]. If it is true, the code inside the if block will execute.
[note]When only one line of code is in the if block, the curly braces can be omitted.
For example:
if (x > y)
  Console.WriteLine("x is greater than y");[/note]

[h1]Relational Operators[/h1]

Use[b] relational operators[/b] to evaluate conditions. In addition to the less than (<) and greater than (>) operators, the following operators are available: [img id="2455" width="100%"]
[b]Example:[/b] [code format="cs" codeId="828"]if ([b]a == b[/b]) {
  Console.WriteLine("Equal");
}
// Displays Equal if the value of [b]a[/b] is equal to the value of [b]b[/b][/code]

