quizzes.textContent:
[h1]The else Clause[/h1]

An optional [b]else [/b]clause can be specified to execute a block of code when the condition in the [b]if [/b]statement evaluates to [b]false[/b].
[b]Syntax: [/b][code format="cs" ]if (condition) 
{
   //statements
}
[b]else [/b]
{
   //statements
}[/code]
For example: [code format="cs" codeId="829"]int mark = 85;

[b]if[/b] (mark < 50) 
{
   Console.WriteLine("You failed.");
}
[b]else [/b]
{
   Console.WriteLine("You passed.");
}

// Outputs "You passed." [/code]

